randoop.types

Class SimpleClassOrInterfaceType

  • java.lang.Object
    • randoop.types.GeneralType
      • randoop.types.ReferenceType
        • randoop.types.ClassOrInterfaceType
          • randoop.types.SimpleClassOrInterfaceType

  • public class SimpleClassOrInterfaceType
extends ClassOrInterfaceType
    SimpleClassOrInterfaceType represents a non-generic class, interface, enum, or the rawtype of a generic class. It is a wrapper for a Class object, which is a runtime representation of a type.

      • isAssignableFrom

        public boolean isAssignableFrom(GeneralType sourceType)
        Indicates whether a value of a GeneralType can be assigned to a variable of this type: Variablethis = Expressionsourcetype. In other words, whether this is a legal assignment.

        Based on the definition of assignment context in section 5.2 of the JDK 8 Java Language Specification a value of one type is assignable to a variable of another type if the first type can be converted to the second by

        • an identity conversion (section 5.1.1),
        • a widening primitive conversion (section 5.1.2),
        • a widening reference conversion (section 5.1.5),
        • a boxing conversion (5.1.7), and
        • an unboxing conversion (section 5.1.8) possibly followed by a widening conversion.
        And, if after all those conversions, the type is a raw type, an unchecked conversion may occur.

        When working on this method, be aware that the method Class.isAssignableFrom(Class) checks identity and reference conversions, and does a comparison of raw types for parameterized types. The method PrimitiveTypes.isAssignable(Class, Class) checks identity and primitive widening for primitive types.

        For ReferenceType, checks for widening reference conversion. See section 5.1.5 of JLS of JavaSE 8 for details.

        Specifically checks for boxing conversion (section 5.1.7)
        Overrides:
        isAssignableFrom in class ReferenceType
        Parameters:
        sourceType - the type to test for assignability
        Returns:
        true if this type can be assigned from the source type, and false otherwise

      • getSuperclass

        public ClassOrInterfaceType getSuperclass()
        Description copied from class: ReferenceType
        Return the type for the superclass for this type. Returns null for types that do not have a superclass. Provides the default for reference type objects, which is the Object type. (Note that this is different behavior than in reflection classes, where null is returned because Object has no superclass.)
        Overrides:
        getSuperclass in class ClassOrInterfaceType
        Returns:

      • getInterfaces

        public java.util.List<ClassOrInterfaceType> getInterfaces()
